    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Process_Main_LoadMeterBills2",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to handle various aspects of meter billing processing within a database schema. It orchestrates the execution of several other stored procedures, each responsible for different parts of the billing process, such as saving transactions, processing original bills, handling rebills, generating bill print summaries, and checking for service classification discrepancies. Additionally, it includes queries to validate energy usage and insert net metering attributes."
        }
